-- New York City Temperature Reaches 101 for Second Day, Weather Service Says
-- Brian K. Sullivan
-- 2010-07-07T18:52:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/new-york-city-temperature-reaches-101-for-second-day-weather-service-says.html

          
          
             Temperatures in New York City soared
to 101 degrees in Central Park for the second day in a row,
breaking the record for the date of 98 set in 1986 and tied in
1993, the National Weather Service reported shortly before 3
p.m. The high yesterday reached 103, three degrees shy of an
all-time high.  
